      "id": "PopularPost318619",
      "post_content": "@NuckChorris: Land destruction is useful as an answer to things like [Valakut](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Valakut), and single discard can be extremely useful if your opponent is down to one card in hand in a control deck and you want to cast something with the guarantee it won't get countered. (There are other similar situations, and it's an antitrip at worst)",
